    <text id="A0548T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McCorkle's letter to his brother [in-law?] complains about delays in the mail
                    system, as asks about his brother's family.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    A. B. McCorkle <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>, 22 February 1858 <lb/>Mr. James Bumgardner,
                    Greenville, Augusta County, Virginia
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1858-02-22">Feby 22, 1858</date>
                        <name type="place">Talladega</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Bro</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You letter of <abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr> 9 has just come to hand. I am
                    surprised that you had not <abbr expan="received">rec<hi rend="super"
                    >d</hi></abbr> my letter written some time ago acknowledging receipt of your
                    draft. We have had immense floods which I suppose have delayed the mails and at
                    this place we have instead of a <abbr expan="Post">P.</abbr> Master an
                    incompetent boy who does not know how to send letters to their proper
                    destination.</p>

                <p>I sold the draft for three <unclear>prct</unclear> just what it cost you so that
                    nothing was lost. Your letter came in the midst of a most interesting meeting
                        <pb n="2"/>and also one from <unclear>S</unclear> I am glad to hear that
                    your daughters are nearly through with school. I hope they will prove a comfort
                    to you and sister and that you will not have occasion to regret what you have
                    done for them. My love to all.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yoru Affect Brother</salute>
                    <signed>A. B. McCorkle</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">If you have to give <unclear>A Pct</unclear> please buy
                        and send one. Yours Fraternally A.B.M</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
